  "response": "Okay, here are some small restaurant chains in Dallas with generally under 10 locations (though some might fluctuate a bit due to openings/closings).  This is based on my current knowledge and research, but things can change quickly in the restaurant world!\n\n**American/Comfort Food/Casual:**\n\n*   **Maple & Motor:** Known for their classic burgers. (2 locations)\n*   **Kuby's Sausage House European Market & Deli:** German cuisine and deli items. (2 locations)\n*   **Rise Souffl\u00e9:** Specializing in souffl\u00e9s. (2 locations)\n*   **Original Market Diner:** A classic diner experience. (2 locations)\n*   **Lucky's Cafe:** Comfort food breakfast and lunch. (2 locations)\n\n**Pizza/Italian:**\n\n*   **Zalat Pizza:** Unique and creative pizza toppings. (8 locations)\n*   **Cane Rosso:** Neapolitan-style pizza. (6 locations)\n*   **i Fratelli Pizza:** Thin crust pizza, catering focus. (7 locations)\n\n**Mexican/Tex-Mex:**\n\n*   **Mi Cocina:** Upscale Tex-Mex. (6 locations)\n*   **Meso Maya Comida y Copas:** Interior Mexican cuisine. (6 locations)\n*   **Rusty Taco:** Simple and affordable tacos. (7 locations)\n*   **Torchy's Tacos:** Austin based, but with a strong presence in Dallas. (9+ locations, so maybe bordering on too big)\n\n**Asian:**\n\n*   **Monkey King Noodle Co.:** Northern Chinese street food. (2 locations)\n*   **Ichiro Ramen Shop:** Ramen restaurant. (2 locations)\n\n**Other:**\n\n*   **Whistle Britches:** Specializing in fried chicken. (3 locations)\n*   **Unleavened Fresh Kitchen:** Healthy salads, wraps, and bowls. (5 locations)\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Location Counts Can Change:** Restaurant groups open and close locations frequently. I'd always recommend double-checking their website or Google Maps for the most up-to-date information.\n*   **Franchises:** Some of these *might* be franchises, even if they're locally owned.\n*   **Definition of \"Chain\":** The line between a very successful single-location res